{
  "stem": "17.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They were only unless I was very sure that I can rely, I knew the principles and ideas of my friend, I wouldn't expose myself [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] to this anti-Semitism being alone, being a minority in a group of friends.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So as we were practically forced, a group of my friends were mostly Jewish girls.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was growing-- graduate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, I started talking about the childhood, that naive children don't know anything.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Later, disappointed girl that her 10-year-old girlfriend is not as what I expected her to be.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that was also rather childish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But as we grew up, and we were coming closer to all this strength, it was more and more obvious.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was-- you know, when it really started to increase, that was because the trends were coming from Germany, which this part was greatly embraced in my own country.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was probably '35, '36 that the anti-Semitism was more obvious.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Some of the Jewish businesses, they were boycott.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I mean, they wouldn't let the shoppers go to the store because that was a Jewish [NON-ENGLISH], Jewish business.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were separation in schools.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was, at first, put very mildly, equal but separate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On universities, in colleges, there were Jewish students-- some of the colleges-- were permitted only to sit on the left side of the room and towards the end.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that was definite separation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was economical, intellectual, social.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But, still, it was a pretty strong Jewish community, quite independent, so that was-- I would even say, it was a pleasant life maybe in the view of a young girl, 15, 16, 17-year-old.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Did your parents have any plans to go  into hiding or to leave the country?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
